<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-13T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-13T03:00:00-05:00" n="597" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2613: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-13T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            13, 1920—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January
                                    14—2:20 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>12. Your December 20, 4 p.m.<note n="65" xml:id="d597fn65"><ref target="frus1919v01#pg_548"><hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p.
                                        548</ref>.</note> and Legation’s December 31, noon.<note n="66" xml:id="d597fn66">Reporting: “[C. L. L.] Williams now
                                    definitely appointed Co-Director General of the Wine and Tobacco
                                    Administration from December 1st.” (File no.
                                    893.51/2598.)</note> Unless the Pacific Development Corporation
                                acts upon its loan option, the influence of Williams in
                                reorganization of wine and tobacco bureau will probably be
                                insufficient to accomplish the <pb facs="0716" n="618" xml:id="pg_618"/> desired result. It trust[s] that the
                                Department will consider carefully its attitude toward the loan and
                                send me instructions as soon as possible in order to relieve the
                                Legation from an embarrassing situation.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>